fz1665702672861.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/efz1665702672861.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/efz1665702672861.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"efz1665702672861\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The [install] section of the initialization file contains information about the\n      current installation.</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"efz1665702672861__section_w3132ab1b5b3_w3133ab1b5_w3134ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1004878e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"efz1665702672861__p_d145037e1_d145038e1_d145039e1\">When Uniface is installed, information about the installation is recorded in the [install] section. (On Microsoft Windows platforms, this information is also stored in the Registry. )</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"efz1665702672861__p_d145040e1_d145041e1_d145042e1\">After installation, you can modify some of these settings, such as <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Project</span> and <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">Browser</span>, which are developer preferences. Other settings should not be modified.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527126\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527126\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "[install] Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated März 22, 2023 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The [install] section of the initialization file contains information about the current installation. Description When Uniface is installed, information about the installation is recorded in the [install] section. (On Microsoft Windows platforms, this information is also stored in the Registry. ) After installation, you can modify some of these settings, such as Project and Browser , which are developer preferences. Other settings should not be modified. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}